Enable passing enums to/from FFI modules.
```
#[ffi(
    module = "test",
    def = "enum TestEnum { A, B }"
)]
impl TestModule {
    #[ffi_export(def = r#"function test_enum(e enum TestEnum) enum TestEnum"#)]
    fn test_enum<E: Engine>(
        _ctx: &CommandContext<'_>,
        _eng: &mut E,
        e: TestEnum,
    ) -> Result<TestEnum, MachineError> {
        Ok(e)
    }
}
```

```
enum Status { A, B }
fact Foo[s: enum Status] => { s string }
action a() {
    let f = unwrap query Foo[s: Status::A] => {}
}
```

Functions now ensure that all types (including argument types and return type) in the signature are actually defined. So, the following now produces an `NotDefined("struct Nonexistent")` error.
```
struct Foo {}
function get_foo() struct Nonexistent {
    return Foo {}
}

function get_bar(e enum Undefined) int {}
```

Closes #163. `if` expression arms are now block expressions, e.g.
```
let x = if y > 0 {
    let x = y + 1
    : x
} else { :0 }
```

Allows `match` to be use as an expression. E.g.:
```
let x = match n {
    1 => {
      :"one"
    }
    _ => "other"
  }
```
